          "ineffective_date": null,
          "title": "Definitions",
          "html": "<p><strong>1.1.3.2. Definitions</strong></p><p>In this Code,</p><p><em>Alternative measure</em> means a substitute for a provision of this Code, other than Part 8, that will achieve the level of performance required by the applicable objectives and functional statements attributed to the provision for which the alternative measure is a substitute.</p><p><em>Private sewage disposal system</em> means a sewage system, other than a building sewer that connects to a municipal sewer, that serves only one lot.</p><p><em>Sewage system</em> means a works for the collection, transmission, treatment and disposal of sewage, other than a main sewer, a combined sewer, a storm sewer or a sewage treatment facility regulated under the <em>Ontario Water Resources Act</em>.</p>",
